健身环变得这么贵，和中国有什么关系？。
Fitness rings have become so expensive, and what has China to do?
栓子。
Thrombolts.
文化。
Culture.
在可预见的未来，中国的游戏市场将一直扮演这个巨大而隐秘的变量。
For the foreseeable future, China's gaming market will continue to play this huge and secretive variable.
。
.
在过去的两个月里，《健身环大冒险》已经成为最完美的理财产品了。
In the past two months, Fitness Ring Adventure has become the perfect financial management product.
。
.
如果你在去年刚发售时原价购入，现在可以用接近三倍的价格再卖给别人。
If you bought it at the original price when you first sold it last year, you can now resell it for nearly three times the price.
这还是近几天价格回落之后的情况：二月下旬，疫情还没有迎来拐点，快递也没有完全恢复运力的时候，《健身环大冒险》的价格一度达到了1800元以上，价格比原价的三倍还高。
That's after prices fell in recent days: by the end of February, before the epidemic reached its inflection point and courier service had not fully recovered capacity, Fitness Ring Adventure had cost more than 1,800 yuan, more than three times the original price.
。
.
前一阵子的价格，最近稍微回落了一些。
The price of a while ago, has receded a little recently.
每年都有这么多游戏发售，可这么长时间过去不仅没打折还升了值的，好像也只此一家。
Every year there are so many games on sale, but so long past not only did not discount but also increased the value of the seems to be the only one.
。
.
我和很多人的感觉一样，健身环刚出的那阵子觉得“有点小贵，等过段时间降价收二手”，然后就错愕地看着它越涨越高。
I feel the same way as many people do. When I first started my workout loop, I thought it was "a little expensive, waiting for a while to reduce prices and get used to it."
。
.
接下来，除了安慰自己“这是虚高，产能一上来肯定马上降”之外，我也只能对着因为过年和疫情迅速起飞的价格望洋兴叹：早知如此，我肯定先买它个百八千份囤着！。
Then, in addition to consoling myself with the fact that "this is virtual height and capacity is sure to be healthy as soon as production capacity is up," I can only exclaim at the rapidly rising prices due to the Lunar New Year and the epidemic: That's for sure, I'll buy a hundred and eight thousand copies of it, according to the source.
有的人还在感叹，但有的人已经开始行动了。
Some people are still exclamation, but some people have already started to act.
国内游戏自媒体的老朋友，对东亚游戏界一直很关注（但消息经常不太靠谱）的分析师“诸葛亮”Daniel，在之前就发了条推特，说中国的商家正在全球扫荡《健身环大冒险》的库存，就为了在国内卖出高价，有图有真相。
Zhuge Liang, an old friend in the media who has been watching the East Asian gaming world (but the news is often unreliable), tweeted earlier that Chinese businesses were scouring the stock of Fitness Ring Adventures around the world in an attempt to get the truth out of high prices at home.
。
.
与此同时，许多媒体的目光也集中到了国内的这场“健身环淘金热”中。
At the same time, a lot of media attention also focused on the domestic "fitness ring gold rush."
比如《南华早报》旗下的Abacus News前两天还刊载了一篇报道，说“甚至仿制的健身环都在中国缺货了”。
For example, the South China Morning Post's Abacus News ran a story two days ago saying that "even imitation fitness loops are out of stock in China."
。
.
在这种情况下，也难免有人把《健身环大冒险》在世界各地的缺货现象和中国买家联系起来了。
In this case, it is hard to avoid linking the "Fitness Ring Adventure" shortage around the world with Chinese buyers.
在一些外媒的报道里，干脆直接把中国的商家称为“scalper”（黄牛党的意思），认为全球到处扫货的他们也算是造成缺货的原因之一。
In some foreign media reports, Chinese businessmen are simply referred to as "scalper" (meaning scalper), and they think they are the cause of the global shortage of goods.
。
.
那么，问题来了——《健身环大冒险》变得这么贵，和中国有什么关系？。
So the question arises - how does "Fitness Ring Adventure" become so expensive and what does it have to do with China?
简单来说，一件商品要涨价，最主要的原因无非两种：想买的人多，能卖的货少。
Simply put, the main reason for a commodity to go up in price is two things: more people want to buy, less goods to sell.
健身环在中国，不仅把这两个原因占全了，还持续了几个月的时间。
The fitness ring in China not only accounts for both of these factors, but also lasts for several months.
。
.
先说前者，想买《健身环大冒险》的人，到底多到什么程度了呢？。
First say the former, want to buy "Fitness Ring Adventure" people, how much more?
我们可以从任天堂1月底发布的财报里见到点端倪：仅仅去年10到12月，日美欧三个主要市场就卖出了170万份以上，东亚市场最给面子，甚至到了“尽管一直出货，但短缺还是存在”的程度。
We can see this in Nintendo's late January earnings report: from October to December alone, Japan, the US and Europe sold more than 1.7 million copies in three major markets, most honourably in East Asia, to the point where "there is still a shortage, even though it has been shipped."
。
.
我们也都知道，在健身环还未正式引进的情况下，大陆肉眼可见的热度带来的这些销量，大部分都是要被算到港台地区或者日本、韩国的数据里去的。
As we all know, in the absence of a formal introduction of fitness rings, most of these sales from the visible heat of the mainland would have to be accounted for in Hong Kong and Taiwan, or in Japan and South Korea.
。
.
这样高涨的需求，来自健身环的定位。
This high demand comes from the positioning of the fitness rings.
。
.
在Switch两年多的生涯中，有过不少人气高到出圈，成功吸引原本不是玩家群体的用户买单的游戏。
Over the course of your two-year career, Switch has experienced a surge of popularity that has attracted gamers who aren't otherwise paying for their games.
而健身环的出圈方式，也是早就被验证过的——2018年底发售的《健身拳击》，就曾经掀起过一阵“打拳热潮”。
And the fitness ring out of the loop, has long been verified - 2018 end of the sale of "Fitness Boxing," once set off a "boxing boom."
。
.
相比之下，设计更友善，互动感更强，其实就是把这条路再走了一遍。
By contrast, being friendlier and more interactive means actually taking the road one more time.
无论是从微博，很多人都是用它带原本不玩游戏的家人和朋友们入了坑。
Whether from microblogging, many people use it to take family and friends who did not originally play games into the pit.
。
.
疫情带来的影响，也进一步激发了我们的购买欲。
The impact of the epidemic has further stimulated our desire to buy.
过年加防疫，被动宅在家里的日子，体重增加的恐惧总是如影随形，你会因为什么去买健身卡，就也会为了同样的理由把钱掏给健身环。
The fear of weight gain is always with you during the New Year plus immunization, when you're in a passive home environment. If you buy a fitness card, you'll pay for the same reason.
。
.
微博、抖音甚至Keep等社交平台上，人们纷纷加入了健身环的安利大军。
On social platforms such as Weibo, Chatter and even Keep, people are joining Amway's army of fitness rings.
。
.
然而，在这样高企的人气下，《健身环大冒险》的供货量却从来没有充足过，这也打破了玩家们“早买早享受，晚买享折扣”的惯性，让它奔着“理财产品”的道路一去不复返。
Yet with so much sentiment, Fitness Ring Adventure has never had enough to offer, breaking the habit of "buy early, buy later, discount later" and setting it on a path to "wealth management products."
。
.
在年前，缺货的主要原因十分简单：就是产能没跟上。
Until a few years ago, the main reason for the shortage was simple: lack of capacity to keep up.
任天堂起初对健身环的销量预估比较保守，这使得初期的备货量就不够充足，再加上健身环本身需要特殊配件的支持，这让它很难迅速提升产量。
Nintendo's initial sales forecasts for the ring were conservative, leaving the initial supply inadequate and the ring itself needing special accessories to support it, making it difficult to boost production quickly.
为此，任天堂还在游戏发售一个多月之后发表了致歉公告，说到年底前都会加大出货量。
To that end, Nintendo issued an apology more than a month after the game's launch, saying it would increase shipments by the end of the year.
。
.
可接下来，春节和新冠疫情叠在一起，就变成了一套缺货组合拳。
But then, the Spring Festival and the new crown epidemic together, has become a set of short-of-stock combination boxing.
过年的各种元素，不管是放假休闲还是阖家团圆，都既是买健身环的理由，也是生产能力下降的原因；而随后疫情带来的隔离，更是把国内的相关产能降到了谷底。
The elements of New Year's Eve, whether holiday or family reunion, are both the reason for buying fitness rings and the decline in production capacity, and the subsequent quarantine brought down domestic production capacity.
。
.
从健身环到Switch，都在疫情中遭了秧。
From fitness rings to Switch, people are suffering from the epidemic.
能搞到的货源越来越少，想买的人却越来越多，于是国内的商家们也只能八仙过海，各显其能。
Can obtain fewer and fewer supplies, want to buy more and more people, so the domestic businessmen can only eight fairy across the sea, each show his ability.
但本质上，这也不过是去搬空其他国家和地区的货架——毕竟《健身环大冒险》还没正式引进呢。
But, in essence, it is simply a matter of emptying shelves in other countries and regions - the Fitness Ring Adventures, after all, have not yet been officially introduced.
。
.
一位对游戏零售电商比较了解的朋友告诉我，现在电商平台上的店铺，进货主要有两种来源：第一种是向负责从香港或日本等地进口的经销商进货，这也是主要的来源；第二种则是自己在各个地区的亚马逊等电商网站，甚至是国内的闲鱼等平台零散收货，再转手卖出。
A friend who knows a lot about the retail and games business told me that there are two main sources of store purchase: the first is from distributors responsible for imports from Hong Kong or Japan, which is the main source; the second is their own regional Amazon and other electronic commerce sites, or even domestic platforms such as fish scattered to sell.
。
.
经销商能提供的货源越来越有限，商家们就只能加大自己搜货的力度。
Dealers can provide more and more limited sources of goods, merchants can only increase their own search efforts.
就这样，大家拉上了全世界人民陪我们一起缺货——先是海淘常见的地区被一扫而空，然后随着需求越来越大，就连一些冷门市场也成为了目标。
In this way, people from all over the world join us in stock-outs - first areas of the sea are swept away, and then, as demand increases, even a few niche markets become targets.
一位在荷兰留学的同学向我表示，二月中旬的时候还能在当地的亚马逊上买到原价的《健身环大冒险》，一个星期之后就也进入要么缺货要么高价的状态了。
A student studying in the Netherlands told me he would be able to buy the original "Fitness Ring Adventure" from the local Amazon in mid-February, and would be out of stock or overpriced within a week.
。
.
我还拜托在日本的朋友去问了一下Bic Camera（日本最大的家电零售企业之一）的店员，得到的答复也有一些参考价值：实体店常年脱销，但每个月会不定时地补货，至于更容易被国内商家扫荡的网络平台，则基本不会有补货了。
I also asked my friends in Japan to ask Bic Camera, a clerk at one of Japan's largest home appliance retailers, if you have a response: entities are out of stock all year round, but restock them every month.
。
.
日本各大电商平台，健身环的价格也在同步上涨。
Japan's major electrical business platforms, fitness ring prices are also rising in step.
那么，回到前面的那个问题：《健身环大冒险》变得这么贵，和中国人到底有什么关系？。
So, back to the question before you: What's the relationship between "Fitness Ring Adventure" and the Chinese people?
你既可以得出一个很简单的答案，也可以发现一个更复杂的版本。
You can either come up with a very simple answer or you can find a more complex version.
。
.
简单点说，你我这些中国消费者想买它，可在中国的工厂又生产不出足够的数量，越来越供不应求，当然就贵了。
In a nutshell, you and I Chinese consumers want to buy it, but factories in China can't produce enough of it.
而在这背后，是大陆这个暂时还没法被精确计量的庞大市场，是比玩家还要热情百倍，翻遍全球寻找货源的商家，也是新冠疫情这个特殊时期带来的商业奇观。
Behind this is China, a vast market that cannot yet be measured with precision, a market that is a hundred times more enthusiastic than players, looking around the world for supplies, and a commercial spectacle brought about by this particular period of the new crown.
。
.
我不知道未来再有游戏卖到三倍的价格会是什么时候，但我总觉得，下一次，可能还是会和中国有关。
I don't know when it's going to cost three times as much in the future, but I've always thought maybe next time it's China.
。
.
因为这是一块如此巨大的市场，而这块市场又无法被正式地统计。
Because this is such a huge market, and this market can not be officially counted.
对于扎根在国外的主机游戏产业来说，在可预见的未来，中国的游戏市场将一直扮演这个巨大而隐秘的变量，直到中国主机用户的需求被正视的那一天。
China's gaming market will remain this huge and secretive variable for the foreseeable future, until the day Chinese mainframe users' needs come to the fore.
。
.
